org.greencheek.processio.domain
Class ProcessIO

java.lang.Object
  org.greencheek.processio.domain.ProcessIO

public class ProcessIO
extends Object

Represents the amount of IO that a process has performed. The object stores two values. The previous state and the current state. Two values are stored so that any ProcessIOUsage object can make calculations based on the two values, for example the amount of IO processed in X seconds.

                                            long currentSampleReadBytes,
                                            long currentSampleWriteBytes)
If the ProcessIO object is stored in a Jmx MBean Server, the @ConstructorProperties are used in order to allow a JMX MXBean object to reconstruct the ProcessIO object to map the constructor arguments to match the jmx properties (accessor method) of the object.

Parameters:
previousSampleMills - The previous time in millis the IO values for the process were read
previousSampleReadBytes - The amount of IO the process had performed previously, at the previous time stamp
previousSampleWriteBytes - The amount of IO the process had performed previously, at the previous time stamp
currentSampleMillis - The most recent time in millis the IO values for the process were read
currentSampleReadBytes - The amount of read IO the process has performed from the most recent sample of it's io usage
currentSampleWriteBytes - The amount of write IO the process had performed from the most recent sample of it's io usage
Method Detail

updateCurrentValues

public ProcessIO updateCurrentValues(CurrentProcessIO currentIO)
Given the current amount of IO that the process has been recorded as caused, This will return a new ProcessIO object with the previous (this object's) current io values , as the previous values, and the values in the given CurrentProcessIO object as the most recent, current, values.

Parameters:
currentIO - The current io that has been recorded for the object
Returns:

updateCurrentValues

public ProcessIO updateCurrentValues(long currentSampleMillis,
                                     long currentSampleReadBytes,
                                     long currentSampleWriteBytes)
Given the current amount of IO that the process has been recorded as caused, This will return a new ProcessIO object with the previous (this object's) current io values , as the previous values, and the values in the given as the most recent, current, values.

Parameters:
currentSampleMillis - The time the latest (current) io value were read.
currentSampleReadBytes - The current amount of read io the process has performed since it started
currentSampleWriteBytes - The current amount of write io the process has performed since it started. The io value was retrieve at the given millis
Returns:
A new ProcessIO object that is build from the current objects current io values, which will be set as the previous io, and it's current values taken from the given parameters
